&lt;li&gt;Identify and exploit key system components, including communication channels and firmware memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct vulnerability research on hardened systems and architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft technical reports related to the function, characteristics, and any potential vulnerabilities of the assessed hardware and firmware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rapidly prototype innovative technologies to analyze and exploit target systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconstruct schematics from physical boards and develop hardware-in-the-loop (HIL) environments to test and emulate device behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct protocol and signals analysis utilizing oscilloscopes, spectrum analyzers, and logic analyzers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a diverse range of research and development projects focused on embedded system security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Isolate areas of interest in complex systems with precision and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
