&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two Six Technologies&lt;/strong&gt; is actively seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Embedded Security Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Trusted Electronics &amp;amp; Effects team in Herndon, Virginia. The team is composed of intellectual individuals, passionate about embedded software development, firmware reverse engineering, and low-level system testing. The team is growing and looking for someone with an embedded systems and firmware analysis background who has an understanding of how to perform light reverse engineering to map out undocumented targets and facilitate forward development inside an emulation environment. If you are actively using Ghidra, Python, and QEMU to modify and rehost complex firmware binaries, the team wants to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute directly to delivering technical tasks focused on the reverse engineering and forward development of complex wireless and embedded systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support critical government customers by executing routine binary and file system analysis to help our team map out undocumented target architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate under moderate supervision, making decisions based on precedent and established company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow team practices to translate reverse engineering insights into functional software, enabling successful firmware rehosting and expansion within custom emulation environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
